Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Dice @sweet potato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and @ginger{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @brown rice{1.25%cup}, @water{1.25%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, half the @Bachan's Original Japanese Barbecue Sauce{2.5%ounce} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

Toss bell pepper on empty side of same baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use two sheets; roast sweet potatoes and mushrooms on top rack and bell peppers on middle rack.

Roast on top rack until veggies are just tender, about ~{15%minutes} (they'll finish cooking in Step 5).

== Chili Soy Mayo ==

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and as much @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} as you like.

> TIP: Start with half the chili sauce, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.

== Finishing ==

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. (For 4 servings, remove sheet with sweet potatoes and mushrooms; leave bell peppers roasting.) Using a #spatula{}, carefully toss sweet potato and mushrooms with @sesame seeds{0.5%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving) and remaining Bachan's Original Japanese Barbecue Sauce.

Return to oven until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt; divide between #bowls{}.

Arrange sweet potato and mushrooms and bell pepper over rice in separate sections. Drizzle everything with as much chili soy mayo as you like. Top with scallion greens and remaining @sesame seeds{0.5%tablespoon}. Serve.